<div class="inner">
  <div class="drive-deets">
    <div class="title">
      <h1><%= @drive.drive_title %></h1>
      <h2>Import Family Data</h2>
      <div class="subnav">
      <%= link_to "Drive Home", drive_path(@drive) %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr>
  </div>



  <p>A CSV or Excel file can be used to import family records. Excel formats must be XLS for versions of excel (1997-2003) or XLSX (2007 or later).</p>

  <p>Download an import template in <%= link_to "Excel Format", family_member_imports_path(format: "xls") %>.</p>
  <br>
  <p>If you prefer to use your own CSV file or EXCEL spreadsheet, the following column headers are required:</p>


  <ul id="import_headers">
    <li>first_name</li>
    <li>age</li>
    <li>gender</li>
    <li>size_pants</li>
    <li>size_shirt</li>
    <li>size_dress</li>
    <li>size_shoes</li>
    <li>bio</li>
    <li>family_code</li>
    <li>drop_location</li>
    <p style="color:red !important;font-size:11px;margin:0px !important;padding:0px !important;">**The drop location name must match the name(s) you enter when you create the gift drive.<br>BE SURE TO REMOVE ANY TRAILING WHITE SPACE BEFORE OR AFTER THE DROP LOCATION NAME.</p> 
  </ul>
  <br>
  <p> 
    In addition to these columns, you may also add optional "needs" columns as "need1", "need2", "need3", and so on. Doing so will associate desired gifts/needs with the family member upon spreadsheet import.
  </p>

  


  <br>
  <%= form_for [@drive, @family_members] do |f| %>
  <% if @family_members.errors.any? %>
  <div id="import_errors">
    <h2><%= pluralize(@family_members.errors.count, "error") %> prohibited this import form completing:</h2>
    <ul>
      <% @family_members.errors.full_messages.each do |message| %>
      <li><%= message %></li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <% end %>


  <div id="import_field">
    <%= f.file_field :file, :id => "import_file" %>
    <%= f.submit "Import", :id => "import_blue_link" %>
  </div>
  <% end %>

</div>



